03:25.417 --> 03:29.084
[overlapping shouting]

03:29.084 --> 03:31.250
- Beat your fucking ass.

03:31.250 --> 03:33.792
[shouting continues]

03:33.792 --> 03:35.000
- Asshole!
- I'm gonna kill you!

03:35.000 --> 03:36.583
- Motherfucker!

03:36.583 --> 03:39.250
[shouting continues]

03:39.250 --> 03:40.375
- Fucking bitch!

03:40.375 --> 03:42.542
[tense music]

03:42.542 --> 03:44.542
- Except for the riot leaders,

03:44.542 --> 03:47.084
who were drop-kicked
into solitary.

03:53.917 --> 03:56.209
♪ ♪

03:56.209 --> 03:57.917
By dawn,

03:57.917 --> 04:01.208
peace descended on Oz.

04:08.209 --> 04:09.917
Yeah, right.

04:10.875 --> 04:12.583
- Let me just, uh,
say this about that.

04:12.583 --> 04:14.166
I-I've already started
to put together

04:14.166 --> 04:15.625
a gubernatorial commission

04:15.625 --> 04:18.333
to investigate:
one, the causes of the riot,

04:18.333 --> 04:21.208
two, the criminal activities
of those prisoners involved,

04:21.208 --> 04:24.000
and three, the appropriateness
of the response to it

04:24.000 --> 04:25.375
by Warden Glynn
and his staff.

04:25.375 --> 04:27.167
- Governor, who will
chair the commission?

04:27.167 --> 04:29.001
- Well, uh, I've just spoken
to Alvah Case,

04:29.001 --> 04:31.125
who's the dean of the law school
at Kaufman-Ferber University.

04:31.125 --> 04:34.000
He's agreed to, uh,
lead the investigation.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.375
To my mind, there's no more
respected jurist in the state.

04:36.375 --> 04:38.333
