50:36.291 --> 50:37.917
before it all came down.

50:37.917 --> 50:42.667
You told me that after
McManus fell to the ground,

50:42.667 --> 50:45.042
you...

50:45.042 --> 50:46.667
quote,

50:46.667 --> 50:48.583
"I cradled him in my arms."

50:48.583 --> 50:50.291
End quote.

50:55.250 --> 50:57.291
How could you cradle him

50:57.291 --> 50:59.875
with your arms
behind your back?

51:01.250 --> 51:02.750
- Have you ever been
in a riot?

51:02.750 --> 51:04.208
- No.

51:04.208 --> 51:06.500
- You have to understand
what's involved.

51:06.500 --> 51:10.084
The idea of being a hostage,
the mob mentality.

51:11.625 --> 51:13.333
You get carried away,
you stop being human.

51:13.333 --> 51:15.750
You become part
of something else.

51:19.001 --> 51:22.291
I have made every
mistake there is.

51:22.291 --> 51:25.250
I have fallen in love
with the wrong men,

51:25.250 --> 51:27.083
I had a baby
out of wedlock,

51:27.083 --> 51:30.166
I drank too much,
I snorted too much.

51:30.166 --> 51:31.875
I have done things
to make money,

51:31.875 --> 51:33.667
including this job,

51:33.667 --> 51:35.126
which makes me dread
getting out of bed,

51:35.126 --> 51:37.750
but each time
I made the choice.

51:37.750 --> 51:40.834
I chose to drink,
I chose to stop.

51:40.834 --> 51:44.126
When my husband got abusive,
I chose to walk.

51:44.126 --> 51:46.792
I refuse to be
anybody's victim.

51:49.458 --> 51:51.875
These mistakes I've made,
they are a part of me.

51:51.875 --> 51:55.209
They are like my skin...

51:55.209 --> 51:57.500
and I do not regret
what I've done.

51:57.500 --> 51:59.875
Do you hear me?

51:59.875 --> 52:02.542
No regrets, no remorse.

52:02.542 --> 52:04.166
I just keep going.

52:09.542 --> 52:10.875
What are you gonna do?

52:10.875 --> 52:12.792
- When I know, you'll know.

52:16.834 --> 52:20.583
- She has a young daughter,
a mother in and out of chemo.

52:20.583 --> 52:22.208
- So what, Leo, so what?

52:22.208 --> 52:24.084
- So if you expose the truth,

52:24.084 --> 52:26.583
you destroy this woman's life
and her daughter's

52:26.583 --> 52:28.750
and for what,
Scott fucking Ross?!

52:28.750 --> 52:29.917
Come on now Alvah,
please.

52:29.917 --> 52:32.126
- What do you want
me to say, Leo?

52:32.126 --> 52:35.458
- To say that Ross died
like the others,

52:35.458 --> 52:37.583
from bullets fired by
a member of the S.O.R.T. Team

52:37.583 --> 52:39.667
in the performance
of his duty.

52:40.834 --> 52:42.333
- I just read the preliminary
draft of your report.

52:42.333 --> 52:43.667
- Yeah, what's wrong?

52:43.667 --> 52:45.333
- You recommend not filing
charges against Said

52:45.333 --> 52:47.084
and the other riot leaders?!

52:47.084 --> 52:49.834
- From a legal standpoint,
the evidence is circumstantial.

52:49.834 --> 52:51.959
From a moral standpoint,
it's laughable.

52:51.959 --> 52:55.250
- I want those bastards
on trial, on TV!

52:55.250 --> 52:57.083
- Look, Governor,
as far as I can see,

52:57.083 --> 52:58.875
whatever they did came about

52:58.875 --> 53:00.709
as a direct result
of your actions!

53:00.709 --> 53:03.084
- You exonerated me.
- Oh, yeah, yeah.

53:03.084 --> 53:05.792
Your commission behaved
like good little boys,

53:05.792 --> 53:07.917
but you can't have it both ways.

53:07.917 --> 53:11.000
If the prisoners are guilty,
so are you.

53:14.917 --> 53:17.166
- This is not the kind
of attitude I expect

53:17.166 --> 53:19.084
from an attorney general.

53:19.084 --> 53:23.208
- Yeah, well,
I've thought about it...

53:23.208 --> 53:24.959
♪ ♪

53:24.959 --> 53:27.792
I don't want to
be attorney general.

53:27.792 --> 53:29.917
I want to be governor.

53:29.917 --> 53:32.041
- [scoffs] What?

53:32.041 --> 53:36.000
- I'll see you on
the campaign trail, Devlin.

53:36.000 --> 53:38.125
Now...
[sniffs]

53:38.125 --> 53:40.792
I've got a press
conference to do.

53:43.000 --> 53:45.001
♪ ♪

53:45.001 --> 53:47.542
[door opens, slams]

53:49.000 --> 53:52.417
[camera shutters clicking]
It is the considered opinion

53:52.417 --> 53:55.042
of this commission

53:55.042 --> 53:57.166
that though the riot itself

53:57.166 --> 54:02.834
and the deaths that followed
are tragic,

54:02.834 --> 54:05.500
no one in particular
is at fault.

54:05.500 --> 54:08.167
[overlapping reporter questions]

54:08.167 --> 54:10.959
We do feel
that there are certain measures

54:10.959 --> 54:14.834
that can be taken to insure

54:14.834 --> 54:17.417
that an event like this

54:17.417 --> 54:19.625
does not happen again.

54:33.583 --> 54:35.000
- Bitch.

54:35.959 --> 54:37.001
- [smooches]

54:40.625 --> 54:44.166
- So as it turns out,

54:44.166 --> 54:46.458
no one was to blame
for the riot.

54:48.625 --> 54:51.208
In fact,
if no one was to blame,

54:51.208 --> 54:55.333
that means nothing
bad happened.

54:55.333 --> 54:58.126
Nothing at all happened.

54:58.126 --> 55:02.209
So life can pretty much
go on as it has before.

55:03.291 --> 55:06.583
Yeah, right.

55:08.917 --> 55:11.917
[tense jazzy music]

55:11.917 --> 55:18.959
♪ ♪

56:05.917 --> 56:08.250
[bright tone]
